UserTerritory2AssocLog.name: UserTerritory2AssocLog
UserTerritory2AssocLog.description: Represents a log of when a user is assigned and unassigned from a territory.

EndDate.description: Date when the user is unassigned from a territory. If the end date is empty, the user is still assigned.

Name.description: Auto-generated unique name of the log.

RoleInTerritory2.description: Userâ€™s role in the territory between the start and end date. The picklist is, by default, empty. Add values to this field using Object Manager.

StartDate.description: Date the user is assigned to the territory.

Territory2Id.description: ID of the territory associated with the log.

Territory2ModelId.description: ID of the territory model associated with the log.

UserId.description: ID of the user associated with the log.

UserTerritory2AssocLog.accessRules: To see this object, enable Sales Territory and User Tracking on the Territory Settings page. Activate a territory model to start the tracking.
